Bank Negara Malaysia

from BUSINESS TIMES, The New Straits Times Press (Malaysia) Berhad,
     30 Sep 1996, page 6

BANK Negara Malaysia is shedding about a quarter of its work force and
closing down half its branches throughout the country in a restructuring
exercise aimed at increasing productivity and efficiency.
  Deputy Prime Minister and Finance Minister Datuk Seri Anwar Ibrahim said
Bank Negara has informed him the need to revamp its operations and close
down several redundant branches.
                               

