PJ Dev expects another good year

from BUSINESS TIMES, The New Straits Times Press (Malaysia) Berhad,
     30 Sep 1996, page 6

PJ DEVELOPMENT Holdings Bhd forsees another good year in 1997 with
earnings emanating from its property development, construction,
manufacturing and hotel divisions.
  Chairman Datuk Dzulkarnain Shafiee in its latest annual report says PJ
Development during the last quarter of this year will be launching a new
apartment development in its Damai Laut Country resort in Lumut.
  Phase one of the development will comprise 180 units of apartments of
various design ranging from studio suite to two bedroom types.
  He says as the development of the resort progresses, phase two and three
would be introduced.
  Looking at its financial position, PJ Development has posted a 69 per
cent higher consolidated pre-tax profit of RM36.88 million for the year
ended June 30 1996 compared to RM21.81 million in 1995.
                               

