Pacific Chemicals Bhd

from BUSINESS TIMES, The New Straits Times Press (Malaysia) Berhad,
     30 Sep 1996, page 7

PACIFIC Chemicals Bhd's proposed assignment of a leasehold industrial land
and reimbursement of construction costs in relation to the factory
buildings and power generator rooms constructed on the leasehold
industrial land has been approved by the Foreign Investment Committee.
  The company on March 20 1996 announced that its wholly-owned subsidiary
- Usama Industries Sdn Bhd - had entered into a deed of assignment with
Equatorial Timber Industries Sdn Bhd (ETI) for the assignment of leasehold
land in Tanjung Manis Timber Processing Zone for RM2.53 million.
                               

