<A NAME = "38"></A>Copyright
BUSINESS TIMES (MALAYSIA) via NewsNet
September 30, 1996

Prices end lower on US rates fear

from BUSINESS TIMES, The New Straits Times Press (Malaysia) Berhad,
     30 Sep 1996, page 12

SINGAPORE blue-chip stocks closed last week 0.8 per cent lower on Friday
amid an absence of local and overseas incentives after fears of a US
interest-rate rise were disproved.
  The Straits Times Industrials Index (STII) ended the week 16.81 points
down at 2,171.05. The broader All-Singapore index was 2.35 points lower to
529.17.
  Dealers said the market was expected to trade in a narrow range in the
near term, but added that the start of October could see some programmed
buying by institutional investors.
  Average daily turnover fell to 68.79 million shares worth S$187.46
million.
  The week opened on a quiet note with investors trying to digest the
release of lower-than-expected August trade data and awaiting the Federal
Reserve's decision on interest rates.
  Creative was still the top gainer, its share price recording an absolute
increase for the week of S$1.95 to S$7.95.
                               

Copyright 1996 The New Straits Times Press (Malaysia) Berhad



