VIETNAM: Cloudy Windows

from BUSINESS VIETNAM, November 1, 1996

Microsoft's introduction of a Vietnamese version of its Windows 95
program has resulted in somewhat cloudy results.  Because people in
the north describe technical terms differently from those in the
south there is no uniform technology for all users.  This has left
many users confused and grumbling over the product's $110 retail
price.  Apparently, Microsoft launched its Vietnamese Window
without first ironing out all the bugs.  It wanted the product in
place before launching its Vietnamese Windows 97.  Mircosoft has
got just that plus legions of disappointed users who now look
forward to the real thing.

Copyright 1996 Business Vietnam




