VIETNAM: Degenerate

from BUSINESS VIETNAM, November 1, 1996

Bank officials have been described as a bunch of degenerates and
incompetents by none other than the official Communist Party
newspaper Nhan Dan.  A description that fits many state employees
in Vietnam.  The paper quoted State Bank chief Cao Si Kien who bemoaned
the lack of control over domestic banking activities.  He cited
operational shortcomings (a nice way of explaining away banks that
accept deposits but can't find the money at withdrawal time),
inadequate checks on loans (assets are a bit difficult to quantify
in Vietnam), and the employment of unqualified and `degenerate'
officials (loans are sometimes given on the basis of available sex
and entertainment).

Copyright 1996 Business Vietnam




