VIETNAM: Expansion

from BUSINESS VIETNAM, November 1, 1996

The ADB is loaning Saigon Port $30m as part of a $40m upgrade.
Work has already begun on the three year project which will see
capacity increase by 25%.  Piers will be expanded, new warehouses
built, container facilities improved, and lighting, water, and
drainage revamped.

The upgrade will give Saigon Port an annual capacity of 9 million
tons, with a further 5 million tons added by 2010.

Copyright 1996 Business Vietnam




