November 1, 1996

VIETNAM: Chicken feed

from BUSINESS VIETNAM, November 1, 1996

Farmers in the Mekeng Delta have been growing marijuana as chicken
feed.  As least that is what they told the police who confiscated
1000 kg of cannabis plants during a recent anti-drug sweep.  Police
found it hard to swallow the chicken feed claims of the two old
ladies who had been tending the crop for the past three years.  It
is believed that the cannabis is destined for the local market
where there has been a dermatic surge in drug-taking since Vietnam's
economic reforms really took hold in the last five years.

Copyright 1996 Business Vietnam




